{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2b72c0c4-5dde-4802-ae49-a600d33850f2","content":"There's no workflow file in the current directory, so here's a general guide for the switch:\n\n### 1. Configure your NuGet.org package for trusted publishing\nOn **nuget.org → Manage Package → Trusted Publishers**, add your GitHub repository, specifying:\n- Repository owner & name\n- Workflow filename (e.g., `publish.yml`)\n- Optionally: environment name, branch/tag filters\n\n### 2. Update your GitHub Actions workflow\n\n**Before (API key):**\n```yaml\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg -k ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }} -s https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n**After (OIDC trusted publishing):**\n```yaml\npermissions:\n  id-token: write   # Required for OIDC token\n\nsteps:\n  # ... build & pack steps ...\n\n  - name: Push to NuGet\n    run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg -s https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n    # No API key needed — the OIDC token is used automatically\n```\n\n### Key changes\n| What | Change |\n|---|---|\n| **`permissions`** | Add `id-token: write` at job or workflow level |\n| **`dotnet nuget push`** | Drop the `-k ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }}` flag |\n| **`secrets.NUGET_API_KEY`** | Can be deleted from repo settings once verified |\n| **nuget.org** | Register the repo + workflow as a trusted publisher |\n\n### 3. Optional but recommended\n- Use a GitHub **environment** (e.g., `nuget-publish`) with protection rules, and reference it in the job (`environment: nuget-publish`). This also lets you scope the trusted publisher on nuget.org to that environment.\n\nWould you like me to modify a specific workflow file, or do you have more questions?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6bc59943-4a53-4e96-ac66-e66d8d5a40df","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory appears to be empty. The user is asking a general question about switching from NuGet API key-based publishing to NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC) in GitHub Actions. Since there's no workflow file in the repository, I'll provide guidance based on general knowledge.","outputTokens":539,"requestId":"C80F:17C00:ADD90:D8DA1:69F54B23"},"id":"4f41de56-c90b-4736-9d8c-a917d573bf7e","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:54:06.444Z","parentId":"db1db4de-6228-400d-87fc-54f6fb9a0c9d"}
